Seven bomb blasts hit Jaipur, killing 80 and injuring 200 in a terror attack with foreign connections.
Police sealed state borders and issued high alerts.
Global leaders, including the US and UK, condemned the violence.
French Foreign Minister offered support, while Indian officials blamed Pakistan-based groups.
The attacks reignited fears of Hindu-Muslim tensions.
Previous bombings in Hyderabad and Punjab were also noted.
The blasts targeted markets and temples, leaving a trail of destruction.
The death toll rose to over 50, with many wounded.
Jaipur remains on edge as authorities investigate the heinous act of terrorism.
